our advanced teaching certificate in common core mathematics (k-8) focuses on developing the mathematical knowledge for teaching (k-8) common core standards and mathematical practices. additional emphasis will be placed on pedagogical strategies to foster motivation, engagement, and the development of academic language in mathematics. this certificate program is beneficial for: courses may be taken individually or in combination, with three of the four courses (9 units) required to earn an advanced teaching certificate in common core mathematics (k-8). nine units may be transferred into our master of arts in teaching program. full descriptions of these courses are availble on the sjsu catalog website . for more information, contact dr. patty swanson at patricia.swanson@sjsu.edu . phone: 408-924-3771 email: teacher-education@sjsu.edu social media: @sjsulurie 